						               													<description>Drums and Muskets have been designed to introduce new players into wargaming.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These rules are designed for the following wars, although players could easily use them as a framework for other wars in the same period.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The Revolutionary Wars (1792-1802).&amp;#10;     Napoleonic Wars (1803-1815).&amp;#10;     The South American Wars of Liberation. (1808 &amp;ndash; 1828).&amp;#10;     The Crimean War (1853-1856).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules provide more experienced gamers a simple more relaxed way of enjoying the period without the complexities and depth of match play. &amp;#10;These rules are not written to provide a purist simulation of the period, but a game with a flavor for the period. &amp;#10;The rules are designed to use any scale models. To play the games all you need are Six-sided dice (D6), ideally 1D12 although you could use 2D6, your own models, terrain to represent the landscape of your battlefield and a ruler.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
